EXERCISE 1:
Suppose the following sql statement
SELECT JOB_ID, MAX(SALARY)
FROM EMPLOYEE
GROUP BY JOB_ID
Q1) Type a plsql program that displays the corresponding the result of the previous sql query

Q2) Make a change to the code in Q11) in order to display job id, job title, max and min salary

EXERCISE 2
By using the table customer, the attribute %type and case statement, type a PL/SQL program that
asks to enter
- Customer id
And display the following
- Customer id
- Name
- Address,
- City
- Credit limit
- New credit limit
The new credit limit is calculated according to the following sheet
Area code New credit limit
<=400 +4%
>400 and <=600 -3%
>600 +2%
When the customer not in the table , display the message : the customer you entered : …. doesn’ texist
